```python
class Solution:
    def findLargestRectangle(self, heights: List[int]) -> int:
        n = len(heights)
        max_area = 0
        
        stack = []
        for i in range(n):
            while stack and heights[stack[-1]] < heights[i]:
                h = heights[stack.pop()]
                area = (i - stack[-1] - 1) * h
                if area > max_area:
                    max_area = area
                    
            stack.append(i)
        
        return max_area
```
